      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "Good race with a lot of unknowns but sticking with the fit SCARLENA (8) who is overdue for a win, placing in three of her five starts. Close to breaking through and looks tough to stop. ASTILLA (6) is a former Victorian who made her debut at Caulfield Heath and showed good speed before weakening. Makes debut in this area for the new yard on the back of a trial win and expected to give a sight. BOWDENE (1) was runner-up on debut and was put away, then safely held fresh in a run below the debut. Fitter and expected to finish much closer. AUCHTERARDER (4) made his debut earlier in the year and was slow to begin and finished at the tail, beaten four lengths. Will have appreciated the spell and can do much better. CRYPTIC MISTRESS (9) was also safely held on debut before another break and can do much better here.",
